Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.65,1:20:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,they came out of the Hindu religion
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.65,1:20:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinduism is extremely interesting
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.65,1:20:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason I avoid going to
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.03,1:20:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,India is because I would never return
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.39,1:20:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I've done that
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.10,1:20:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the great truths emerged first on the planet long ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.93,1:21:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of those arose, of course, the fabled yogas, the great yogas, of which what I teach the closest would be J-H-A-N-A yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.35,1:21:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,J-H-A-N-A. J-H-A-N-A yoga, yes, that's the closest.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.31,1:21:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonduality, the pursuit of the ultimate truth, the pathway of nonduality is the closest thing to what we teach.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.77,1:21:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say ours is a modern day version, modern day version of J-H-A-N-A yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.88,1:21:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A bhakti of devotion at 9.35.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.67,1:21:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Raja.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.56,1:21:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoga, karma yoga, selfless service.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.30,1:21:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Selfless service.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.17,1:21:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That is open to all of mankind, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.94,1:21:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,To be a selfless service, before you leave the house, you close the squirrel trap, because he might get caught in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.61,1:22:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd spend the whole day all by himself until he got home.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.60,1:22:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to close the squirrel trap.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.73,1:22:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just, you gotta do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.03,1:22:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You walk by the bug, he's going like this, and you can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.02,1:22:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You just gotta stop and turn him over, and then he walks away, and now you feel happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.02,1:22:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.72,1:22:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Selfless service.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.18,1:22:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Kundalini yoga is 5.10.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.35,1:22:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Kundalini yoga is less because it's like there's an intentionality behind it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.94,1:22:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't recommend trying to force the kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.90,1:22:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.47,1:22:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unwise.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.26,1:22:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Artificial means of trying to achieve the cities on their own.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.57,1:22:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, the fact that you want to be able to do a certain city, no matter what it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.43,1:23:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is already indicative of the spiritual ego, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.63,1:23:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You're gonna take classes on how to fly.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.63,1:23:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a break, will you?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.53,1:23:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're able to fly, you fly.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.39,1:23:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And it happens without your thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.69,1:23:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, kundalini yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.39,1:23:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe in trying.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.53,1:23:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you why.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.27,1:23:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the kundalini energy, the etheric energy, as you advance, it automatically rises.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.97,1:23:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As you see the beetle, and you turn him over, the kundalini energy is risen.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.32,1:23:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.01,1:23:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to do anything artificial.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.35,1:23:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Artificial exercises.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.64,1:23:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe in...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.53,1:23:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to make your energy get higher.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.06,1:23:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Either you're a kindly person, or you're not.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.50,1:23:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're kindly...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.53,1:24:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,towards all of life, you don't have to do strange things to try and force the energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.93,1:24:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you force the energy prematurely, it's a dangerous, I think, dangerous thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.90,1:24:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that you, as a being, are not ready for it yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.39,1:24:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Artificially.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.55,1:24:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the attraction of the spiritual ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.56,1:24:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.84,1:24:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Forcing the kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.81,1:24:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Kriya yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.90,1:24:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Sahaj Maharaj.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.82,1:24:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.56,1:24:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Hatha yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.89,1:24:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hatha yoga is a good place to start.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.27,1:24:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people start with Hatha yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.88,1:24:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't believe in the glamorization of these yogas.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.07,1:24:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You get these slick spiritual magazine, and Leitman is on this call.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.35,1:24:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And it all shows a diaphanous, beautiful woman on the front.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.97,1:24:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Or she's meditating like this, but there's flowers, and music, and bubbles, and all kinds of crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.65,1:25:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,She's always diaphanous.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.42,1:25:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You never see an elderly, wrinkled old lady.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.14,1:25:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you ever get a slick spiritual magazine?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.35,1:25:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,She looks about 83.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.14,1:25:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,She's well overweight.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.42,1:25:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not too good looking.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.06,1:25:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Her hair is sort of a mess.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.38,1:25:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you ever see her?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.43,1:25:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How about middle-aged men?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.06,1:25:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You see any middle-aged men meditating in there?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.93,1:25:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hatha yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.93,1:25:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hatha yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.28,1:25:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the impact of the medium.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.48,1:25:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hatha yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.51,1:25:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the impact of the media, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.40,1:25:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Impact of the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.61,1:25:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody missing an aruba has to be a slim, good-looking blonde, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.10,1:25:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Middle-aged duck walloper with tattoos, you'd never hear about him.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.39,1:25:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Says if he's colored or not white, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.07,1:25:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd never hear about him.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.48,1:25:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see how that invades the spiritual domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.06,1:26:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.75,1:26:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We could talk a lot about the yogas.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.18,1:26:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But because our own pathway of non-duality is one of the classic,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.81,1:26:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the way of devotion towards truth, we won't speak about it because that's what we talk about all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.13,1:26:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hare Krishna, of course, is very well-known.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.38,1:26:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Subhara is less well-known.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.34,1:26:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Siddha Vedanta at 550 is well-known.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.43,1:26:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Sikhism is relatively well-known at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.80,1:26:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's tempting to become a Sikh because I love their turbans.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.72,1:26:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to be a Sikh just for a week and walk around with that turban.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.77,1:26:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really cool, isn't it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.81,1:26:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jainism is sort of arduous.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.14,1:26:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of our best friends in Korea has a meditation center, Rana Suwami.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.72,1:27:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In Jainism, you're not supposed to, you're always walking around that you might step on a bacteria or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.13,1:27:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So I figure let God worry about the bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.00,1:27:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They wear masks so they won't.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.68,1:27:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Breathe in an insect and kill it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.46,1:27:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So that, I think those are people who were once careless of life, careless of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.50,1:27:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And now to get the lesson, they are very careful of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.15,1:27:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,One time you were disregarded the value of life and you stomped it to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.57,1:27:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you see the sacredness of all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.07,1:27:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you're very carefully trained not to step on an ant.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.39,1:27:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I try not to step on an ant because I'm obsessive-compulsive, not because I'm a...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.93,1:27:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want his death on my...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.64,1:27:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Same thing, try not to kill people if you can.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.39,1:28:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just bad karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.10,1:28:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we come to one of the great ones, which is we're very familiar here in Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.43,1:28:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a Buddhist stupa here and a very active spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.72,1:28:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha is very active in Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.60,1:28:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have Mahayana, the way of the greater vehicle, and you have Hinayana,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.97,1:28:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have Zen, Lotus Land.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.52,1:28:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was a consultant to all these things at one time, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.02,1:28:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and back east for a decade.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.38,1:28:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a consultant to the Episcopal Diocese, the Catholic Diocese,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.02,1:28:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the nuns who all lived in seclusion, what do you call them?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.52,1:28:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sequoia, cloistered nuns.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.75,1:28:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Cloistered nuns, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.19,1:28:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, to them, and then also the Zen Monastery, also the Ministerial Council.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.69,1:28:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So I did a lot of counseling with ministers and various peoples.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.61,1:29:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And very often the monastery would send in somebody,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.46,1:29:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is he in Samadhi or Catatonia?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.73,1:29:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we wrote that in the book,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.38,1:29:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,how to differentiate pathologic mental states from spiritual states.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.92,1:29:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Because to the unsophisticated person,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.89,1:29:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,they can look the same, whether a person is in Catatonia or in a state of Samadhi.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.38,1:29:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when you go into a high state, that got me off of, well, it didn't get me off the rock, did it?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.05,1:29:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I sat in a rock in Sedona, and it was a state of incredible bliss, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.51,1:29:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And time went by, and people went by, and the sun came up and the sun went down.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.90,1:29:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can get into a state like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.53,1:29:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the police could have come along and dragged me away, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.89,1:29:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.81,1:29:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a fellow sitting there, spaced, you know, and take you to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.48,1:29:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So I kept surrendering all this.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.00,1:30:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So they take you to the hospital, and they're going to give you a shot of Thorazine.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.61,1:30:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So they give you a shot of Thorazine.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.76,1:30:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not going to affect my spirit, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.00,1:30:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So nothing got me off the rock.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.31,1:30:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Except they had things to do, and out of love for others, I got off the rock.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.30,1:30:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was, the only thing that got me off the rock was love, the love for others.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.84,1:30:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.53,1:30:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It enabled me to function again.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.57,1:30:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so those are the great yogas.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.69,1:30:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We're familiar with these.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.85,1:30:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there's a slight difference, there's a difference between Hinayana and Mahayana,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.61,1:30:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's an artificial separation.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.15,1:30:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you can't be enlightened just for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.11,1:30:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It automatically affects the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.69,1:30:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mahayana, such as the current, what's his name, the head of the Tibetan?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.31,1:30:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Dalai Lama, yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.84,1:30:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He's concerned with the salvation of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.11,1:31:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All of mankind, that's Mahayana.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.56,1:31:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinayana is more, you're concerned with your own enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.06,1:31:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Zen is really in a world of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.76,1:31:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I could spend the entire day talking about Zen, talking about Zen, and the people I've known.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.17,1:31:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a style, in a way.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.84,1:31:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Zen, in a way, is a style.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.43,1:31:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do Zen meditation while you're walking around and talking, just as I am now.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.84,1:31:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The Zen meditative state is continuous.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.68,1:31:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The talking has nothing to do with the state.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.34,1:31:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't interrupt it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.13,1:31:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning, it does interrupt it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.55,1:31:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you get up from meditation, it disappears.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.13,1:31:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Samadhi, certain states.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.72,1:31:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, currently, there's no great teachers of Zen in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.75,1:31:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,None of them calibrate over 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.92,1:31:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the state of Samadhi is not the state of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.85,1:31:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not Satori.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.65,1:31:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.30,1:31:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can go into great states.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.15,1:32:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, so in the beginning,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.90,1:32:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the state comes on when you're in a tense meditative state.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.56,1:32:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, as you open your eyes, it disappears.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.14,1:32:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,After a while, you can open your eyes and the state continues.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.50,1:32:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, when you get up and begin to walk around, it disappears.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.50,1:32:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, in a very advanced state, nothing interferes with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.43,1:32:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a period of time of adjustment, I remember, of some years,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.39,1:32:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,where there wasn't possible to function in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.43,1:32:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, the state returns.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.39,1:32:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Capacity to function.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.68,1:32:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But it has nothing to do with your own...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.86,1:32:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,your own reality and that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.17,1:32:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't affect it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.76,1:32:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a frog jumping about on the top of the lake.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.50,1:32:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with the stillness of the lake.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.10,1:32:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's the frog jumping around that's speaking today.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.52,1:32:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I have nothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.82,1:33:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I, whatever the frog says, I say to myself,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.52,1:33:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,wow, see, cool, man, cool, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.22,1:33:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the Zen Monastery, Hinyana, a lotus land has a...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.13,1:33:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,analogous to Christianity.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.25,1:33:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,As we pointed out, Jesus Christ taught salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.44,1:33:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha taught enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.93,1:33:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotus land is in the approximation of the two.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.84,1:33:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha of infinite mercy acts like the savior.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.64,1:33:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He is your advocate.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.53,1:33:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He is your advocate.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.23,1:33:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotus land is the same as heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.53,1:33:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the view of it is that the negativity of this world
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.76,1:33:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is so severe that reaching enlightenment here is very unlikely.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.15,1:33:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And statistically, that is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.06,1:33:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Practically, it never happens.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.72,1:33:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Whole centuries go by and not one single enlightened being
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.94,1:33:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,on the planet, sometimes for hundreds of years.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.94,1:34:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And because the negativity here is so severe,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.17,1:34:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so the idea of lotus land Buddhism is through good karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.10,1:34:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,When you leave the body next time, you land in a celestial realm.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.81,1:34:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And from the celestial realm, then, where you're not surrounded
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.31,1:34:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,by all this intense negativity, you can transcend on to full enlightenment, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.01,1:34:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And there, your advocate would be Avalokiteshvara or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.98,1:34:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that his name?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.89,1:34:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Avalokiteshvara.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.72,1:34:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a mouthful.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.61,1:34:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever he is, he's there.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.61,1:34:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaks for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.02,1:34:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaks for you just as Christ does in heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.72,1:34:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you know, we've said that there is not just one heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.31,1:34:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There are multiple regions of heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.61,1:34:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is sacrilegious and it'll get me rid out of any religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.26,1:34:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I would like to have an exclusive pipeline.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.02,1:34:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one, each religion is exclusive pipeline.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.02,1:35:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When they say you can only get to heaven if you do so and so,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.22,1:35:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,14 wives or whatever they do, it means to their section, their neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.92,1:35:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So the celestial realm is in the 600s.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.22,1:35:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has, it has...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.48,1:35:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,realms.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.78,1:35:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you leave the body, you gravitate to that which you are automatically.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.59,1:35:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you don't have to be a genius to see that,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.98,1:35:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that you automatically flow to the altitude of that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.21,1:35:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Because like goes to like in the other dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.06,1:35:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are multiple heavens, multiple heavens.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.65,1:35:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure there are heavens where the Vikings went and Valhalla and the various...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.90,1:35:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,places.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.81,1:35:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There's probably even a place where they've got 90 virgins, whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.92,1:36:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You go there, no, there's 70 virgins, 70 virgins.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.78,1:36:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And what they don't tell you is the 70 virgins are 900 years old and they hate men.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.53,1:36:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they're still virgins.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.60,1:36:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And you find out, oops, that was a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.89,1:36:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then you reincarnate.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.10,1:36:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'll become a Protestant next time, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.64,1:36:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.53,1:36:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddhist Land Buddhism, that is very similar to Christian Heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.36,1:36:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Tantric is tricky and I don't recommend Tantric unless you're extremely sophisticated.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.47,1:36:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the Tantric sometimes gets involved with energies and the manipulation of energies.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.14,1:36:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And it thereby becomes linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.17,1:36:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Thereby becomes linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.17,1:36:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When you start manipulating energies on the other side, you're dealing with the linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.56,1:36:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So you brought yourself down.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.67,1:36:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore Tibetan and Tantric have their downsides.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.17,1:37:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,One is 405, and I don't know why it calibrates that way, I'm not that familiar with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.35,1:37:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Another Eastern religion, of course, is Shinto, the sun god, descendant of the sun god.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.02,1:37:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what happens to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.06,1:37:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So Shinto starts out relatively integrous at 350.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.06,1:37:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But then when you include the Sumerian code, it drops to 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.06,1:37:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Kleshud code, it drops to 180.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.64,1:37:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese invasion of Manchuria when I was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.61,1:37:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's always been at war since I've been on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.61,1:37:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, when I was young, the Japanese were slaughtering people in Manchuria.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.02,1:37:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The slaughter of Nanking.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.02,1:37:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And it came out of this code here.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.02,1:37:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Which eliminates mercy as a weakness.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.13,1:38:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, as the prisoners surrender, you slaughter them.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.60,1:38:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.69,1:38:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why Al-Qaeda and all those, because they're exactly the same way.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.85,1:38:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If you surrender, instead of mercy, they cut your head off slowly with a saw.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.03,1:38:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And videotape the proceeding.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.56,1:38:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see being kindly to those people isn't going to do much good.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.97,1:38:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in being kindly, you're going to get your head sawed off.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.97,1:38:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they despise that as weakness.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.57,1:38:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So that code is the same as this code here.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.64,1:38:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who surrender deserve to die by virtue of the fact that they're cowards.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.64,1:38:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore they slaughter the raping Nanking.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.09,1:38:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Slaughter people in the tens of thousands.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.31,1:38:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Taoism is to flow with the flow of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.31,1:38:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,To go how it goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.31,1:38:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,To go how it goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.31,1:38:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,To let it be.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.40,1:39:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The Beatles song, let it be calibrated quite high.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.56,1:39:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sympathy for the devil calibrated quite low.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.46,1:39:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let it be calibrated quite high.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.46,1:39:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let it be is Taoism.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.46,1:39:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To bend with the current.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.59,1:39:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the reed, so that you don't break.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.59,1:39:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Other religions, Baha'i has an appeal from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.77,1:39:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it included women on an equal basis with men.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.77,1:39:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And a lot of the traditional religions, the clergy and everybody are men.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.77,1:39:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the attraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.77,1:39:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction of Baha'i was that men and women were equal.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.80,1:39:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Native American religion is unique in that it didn't have a great savior or great spokesman.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.43,1:39:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddhism had the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.43,1:39:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity had Jesus Christ, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.43,1:39:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Islam had Muhammad.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.60,1:40:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Native Americanism arose spontaneously of its own, not by any authority.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.85,1:40:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So they don't worship authority.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.85,1:40:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just obvious.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.97,1:40:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got all your marbles there.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.30,1:40:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That all arises out of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.30,1:40:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That all of life is divine.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.30,1:40:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So before you kill the antelope, or after you kill the antelope,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.59,1:40:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you thank God for the sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.59,1:40:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that is out of the Rig Veda, which calibrates in the 900s.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.89,1:40:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing surrenders in fulfilling its karmic destiny.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.89,1:40:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Then by its death it subserves
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.69,1:40:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the life that is higher.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.69,1:40:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It earns the right to transcend.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.14,1:40:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, when you eat the cow,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.14,1:40:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the cow in its sacrifice to humanness
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.14,1:40:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,earns the right to karmically return eventually as a human.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.14,1:41:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It is earned karmically by its own sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.30,1:41:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the Rig Veda which calibrates the 900.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.26,1:41:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Each gives its life and thereby ascends
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.15,1:41:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to the life that is higher than it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.15,1:41:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, over a great trajectory of time,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.22,1:41:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the lowest eventually becomes the highest.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.35,1:41:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It earns karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.35,1:41:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And seeing through certain eyes, you see
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.89,1:41:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that the animal willingly does surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.89,1:41:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and sacrifice itself to the higher.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.89,1:41:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have to be able to see that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.61,1:41:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It does, in its spirit, sacrifice itself
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.52,1:41:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to Thee, O Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.52,1:41:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I worship and surrender my life?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.42,1:41:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And by surrendering your life is the very last step
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.42,1:42:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,before the gates open and divinity shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.50,1:42:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To Thee, O Lord, do I surrender life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.06,1:42:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last thing to be surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.06,1:42:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The final doorway.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.55,1:42:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing left.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.55,1:42:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All is still.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.44,1:42:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.68,1:42:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no other there.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.68,1:42:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing remaining is life.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.60,1:42:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And you realize that this too, O Lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.18,1:42:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,must I surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.68,1:42:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And then is the experience of a sudden
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.02,1:42:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and very severe feeling of dying.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.02,1:42:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And you realize that you are dying
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.02,1:42:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and you are dying for the first time ever.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.02,1:42:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't die until this moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.02,1:42:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, the splendor,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.57,1:43:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.72,1:43:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mind is silent forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.85,1:43:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes years to learn how to talk again.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.85,1:43:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.17,1:43:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this intrinsic reality is intuitively
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.93,1:43:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,intuited by the Native American.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.06,1:43:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, is reflecting the wisdom
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.06,1:43:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Rig Veda at 900.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.75,1:43:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The same thing is repeated verbally
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.75,1:43:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Rig Veda many thousand years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.93,1:43:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we move to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:37.14,1:43:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity and avatars.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.14,1:43:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we say angels are 500 and up
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.14,1:43:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and that angels can also appear
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.14,1:43:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in the physical domain in the human body.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.65,1:43:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask that.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.78,1:43:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's who picked me up
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.75,1:44:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,when the truck broke down in the highway.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.75,1:44:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.67,1:44:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people actually sort of channel angelic energies.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.82,1:44:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I am all alone, a million miles from nowhere,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.85,1:44:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,broken down in my old truck,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.85,1:44:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which I still have,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.85,1:44:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,on a busy intersection.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.46,1:44:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And I forget, I had to get to the airport
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.46,1:44:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,for a plane, something bizarre.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.46,1:44:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, there you are broken down
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.46,1:44:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in one of these major metropolitan intersections.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.46,1:44:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh boy, you're lonesome in this old truck.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.13,1:44:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And the car pulls over.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.18,1:44:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:38.28,1:44:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I don't know, it seems to me like the,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.28,1:44:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what it was, the tire, the tire blew.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.28,1:44:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And I couldn't make the jack work,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.18,1:44:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't own a jack, I forget which.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.31,1:44:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, well, I'll take it off for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.67,1:44:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll take it down, the next ramp off,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.67,1:44:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a place that can fix it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.67,1:44:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy, out of nowhere, takes off my tire,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.67,1:45:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,puts it in his truck, drives it down the ramp,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.67,1:45:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,does the circle back, comes back all the way around,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.67,1:45:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe 45 minutes later,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.67,1:45:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and puts it back on my truck.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.57,1:45:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That kind of thing has happened repeatedly in my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.09,1:45:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you channel, you calibrate,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.98,1:45:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was that an angel?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.22,1:45:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.47,1:45:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The man I'm holding in mind, God bless him,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.47,1:45:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,was an angel.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.69,1:45:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.69,1:45:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So some angels choose, apparently,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:30.34,1:45:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to reincarnate,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.17,1:45:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and they are a great source of benevolence in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.17,1:45:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Over and over, this kind of a thing has happened to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.19,1:45:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Inexplicable.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.77,1:45:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If it happened a few times, you could say that's chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.77,1:45:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But when it's a repetitive pattern,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.68,1:45:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not a chance, it's a repetitive pattern.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.68,1:45:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see what happens when you turn over beetles
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.68,1:45:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that are falling on their back?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.68,1:46:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all that happened to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.31,1:46:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a beetle, on my back,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.82,1:46:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,along came an angel, flipped me over,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.82,1:46:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was on my way again.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.82,1:46:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:16.14,1:46:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Angels, 500 and over.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.19,1:46:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangels, 50,000 and up.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.30,1:46:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha nature is 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.84,1:46:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha nature as voidness is 980.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:32.22,1:46:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Native American Great Spirit, 850 plus.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.22,1:46:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Deity itself, 720.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.76,1:46:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm talking about the terms now.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.76,1:46:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yewa and Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.21,1:46:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know historically why Jehovah's 205
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.21,1:46:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with the world the way it was in those years.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.21,1:46:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The word God is an intellectual term.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.81,1:46:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellectual concept is 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:58.85,1:47:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, that's why the Buddha recommended
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.85,1:47:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,not to utilize the terminology at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.85,1:47:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Because everybody's got their own conception of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.85,1:47:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and holding that conception will be a block
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.85,1:47:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in the experiencing of the ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.85,1:47:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the ultimate reality, first of all,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.85,1:47:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is non-linear and not definable,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.85,1:47:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so any concept you have about God
Dialogue: 0,1:47:21.85,1:47:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,has got to be false to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.07,1:47:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,As an intellectual concept,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.07,1:47:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the Buddha said, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.07,1:47:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,do not talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.21,1:47:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha, however, as we see,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.21,1:47:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated extremely high.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:38.21,1:47:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the Buddha was,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:43.64,1:47:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,let's use the term, God-realized.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.35,1:47:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist. See?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:49.35,1:47:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, don't use the word God.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.35,1:47:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The false conclusion that Buddhists make
Dialogue: 0,1:47:53.60,1:47:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is therefore you didn't experience divinity as godness.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.60,1:47:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, he did.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.06,1:48:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, he wouldn't calibrate a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.06,1:48:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, he knew it was God.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.40,1:48:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said, but if you use the term,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.40,1:48:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,so when I tell you what happens
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.56,1:48:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,if you lay down your life,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.56,1:48:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite presence reveals itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.97,1:48:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't use the word God either,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.39,1:48:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because there is no word there.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.68,1:48:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a profound,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.68,1:48:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no word for it, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:29.56,1:48:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the Buddha said,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:31.56,1:48:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,don't use that word.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.68,1:48:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Buddha said a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.73,1:48:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So we got through this.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.73,1:48:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This has to do with
Dialogue: 0,1:48:41.00,1:48:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a Hebrew history.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.57,1:48:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why Jehovah is at 205?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:45.57,1:48:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.73,1:48:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And Yehweh is at 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.73,1:48:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not a biblical scholar.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.73,1:48:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what's usually called religious,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:57.51,1:49:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual research is really archeologic research.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.51,1:49:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's archeologic.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.51,1:49:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Where Jesus walked and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.51,1:49:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Where Jesus walked now and all
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.64,1:49:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates about,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.64,1:49:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to tell you where it calibrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.64,1:49:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, so,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:12.64,1:49:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,God calibrates information
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.02,1:49:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,about infinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:20.02,1:49:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,God the Father,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.02,1:49:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the Creator,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.02,1:49:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the Almighty,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:24.21,1:49:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Maker of Heaven and Earth,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.88,1:49:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Universe,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.15,1:49:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Maker of all things visible and invisible,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:33.15,1:49:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Omnipotent, Omniscient,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:35.96,1:49:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and Omnipresent,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.96,1:49:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the Supreme,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.96,1:49:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the Source of all life and existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.96,1:49:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Essence is the Holy Spirit,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:44.31,1:49:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,referred to as Allah.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:46.31,1:49:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In early Hindu,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:48.50,1:49:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,referred to divinity as An,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.50,1:49:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A-N,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:53.07,1:49:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,expressed as Shiva,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.07,1:49:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Krishna and Brahma,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:57.07,1:49:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and Vishnu.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:59.07,1:50:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Durga is Farah, Rama,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:02.61,1:50:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,God of Moses and Abraham.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:06.73,1:50:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're all talking about the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:08.73,1:50:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,despite all this different languaging.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.73,1:50:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All this different languaging.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.73,1:50:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They all refer to that which is infinite,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:16.18,1:50:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which arises all of creation,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:20.18,1:50:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and creation is continuous and ongoing.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:24.31,1:50:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Has no beginning, has no end.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:27.56,1:50:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah? Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.72,1:50:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:33.93,1:50:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the highest level possible,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:38.68,1:50:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see if that's still so,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.84,1:50:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest level possible for a human within
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.06,1:50:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the human domain is a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.72,1:50:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The human domain is not a good place to be
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.72,1:50:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're over a thousand or so,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.72,1:50:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because you fry your nervous system.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:55.72,1:50:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:57.85,1:50:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I've lost my voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:59.76,1:51:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.93,1:51:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:05.93,1:51:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this indicates the presence of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:51:07.93,1:51:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,within the human domain,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:09.93,1:51:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:12.02,1:51:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So was the Buddha enlightened?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:14.02,1:51:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, were these both the same?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:16.02,1:51:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:18.02,1:51:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They all calibrated at a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:20.06,1:51:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The twelve Christian apostles calibrated about ninety,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:23.06,1:51:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,just less than Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.06,1:51:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The name of God as Om,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:27.51,1:51:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is 970,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.60,1:52:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Satchitananda's translation of Patanjali's
Dialogue: 0,1:52:01.64,1:52:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Richard McCullough,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:04.00,1:52:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it has an error in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:06.40,1:52:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It designates Om as Aum.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:10.76,1:52:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Aum is only about 470, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:13.76,1:52:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Aum is over 400,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:17.02,1:52:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,420, 430, 440,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:21.21,1:52:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,460, it's 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:25.07,1:52:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Aum is an error.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:27.68,1:52:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Satchitananda's translation of
Dialogue: 0,1:52:31.71,1:52:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Patanjali's aphorisms.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.71,1:52:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:36.02,1:52:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The twelve Christian apostles then,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:38.02,1:52:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the bones of St. Peter,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:40.02,1:52:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Basilica in Rome,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:42.02,1:52:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,still calibrate in the high 900s,
